President Obama had a phone conversation with Turkish President Erdogan to discuss the next steps in the fight against ISIL. They recognized Turkey's contributions to the campaign and the need for close coordination between the US and Turkey to build on these successes. They also discussed Turkey's participation in the Counter-ISIL Coalition's efforts in Iraq and affirmed their support for Iraq's sovereignty and territorial integrity. They both agreed on the importance of denying the PKK a safe haven in northern Iraq.